        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-15T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-15T11:00:00-05:00" n="1043" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1043">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Gleysteen, Culver: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Dairen</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Paddock</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dairen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-16T01:00:00+09:00">April 16, 1949—1 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:27 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>109. Chief Soviet Kommandatura today said I receive 2 or 3 days answer to points
                    re Gleysteen arrest (reference immediately preceding telegram); thus no need
                    action last paragraph as yet.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 109; repeated Nanking 75, Moscow 6.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Paddock</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
